## 🚀 Feature: Consent Evaluate API (Admin Server)

### 📌 Description
Implement a Consent Evaluate API in Admin Server to determine consent status for a user.

This API:
- Checks consent in local DB
- Calls Communication Service (EIS Wrapper) when required
- Returns consent status + Privacy Notice + Purpose

Used at:
- MIF Login
- Merchant Panel Login

---

### 🔗 API Details

**Endpoint**

POST /admin/consent/evaluate


**Request Body**
```json
{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "dpCIF": "string",
  "dpMobile": "string",
  "touchPointId": "string",
  "purposeSetId": "string"
}

Response Body

{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "isConsentActive": true,
  "consentStatus": "Active | Inactive | Expired | Revoked",
  "consentReadResponse": {},
  "privacyNoticeResponse": {},
  "purposeResponse": {}
}
⚙️ Flow
Step 1 — Validate Request
Step 2 — Check Local DB

Case: Active Consent

status = ACTIVE
not expired

✅ Return from DB
❌ Do NOT call Communication Service

Step 3 — If Consent Not Active

Call:

Communication Service → Consent Read API
Case A — Consent Active from CCMS
Update local DB
Return:
isConsentActive = true
Case B — Consent Not Active
Fetch Privacy + Purpose
Save in master tables
Compare versions
Update if changed

Return:

isConsentActive = false
Step 4 — Fallback (Service Down)
Read from local DB:
privacy_master
purpose_master

Return:

isConsentActive = false
✅ Acceptance Criteria
 Local DB check works
 Calls Communication Service when needed
 Privacy & Purpose updated on version change
 Fallback implemented
 Response matches contract
 Expiry handled using validityDays

